The paper discusses the role of individual self-efficacy in Information Systems security adoption, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also explores the user's knowledge and skills in applying safeguard measures, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical grounds of the research, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the study evaluates the appropriateness of past empirical investigations, which relates to cybernetics (cs.CY).
